context: The original <a0_0>Cubist architecture is very rare<a0_0/>. There is only one country in the world where Cubism was really applied to architecture – namely <a1_0><b6_0>Bohemia<b6_0/> (today Czech Republic<a1_0/>) and especially its capital, Prague. Czech architects were the first and only ones in the world to ever design original Cubist buildings. Cubist architecture flourished for the most part between 1910–1914, but the <b4_0><b5_0>Cubist or Cubism-influenced buildings<b5_0/><b4_0/> were also built after the World War I. After the war, the architectural style called <a2_0><b3_0>Rondo-Cubism<b3_0/><a2_0/> was developed in Prague fusing the Cubist architecture with round shapes.
